Checks if a number or word is less than another number or word. Word comparison is case-sensitive in alphabetical order.

value2 - The second value.

Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:

notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

91a85c12-884e-40d4-9f86-3a2a2ec1a44c.59eff0ce-82b2-4791-b937-54d51f9361f3.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

91a85c12-884e-40d4-9f86-3a2a2ec1a44c.663f6a1e-3daa-4c89-bf02-5f5c425143d5.prompt=Enter a value for value1 91a85c12-884e-40d4-9f86-3a2a2ec1a44c.754b90bf-425a-464f-87c3-4a51ac87acfe.description=
Evaluates the given 'xpathExpression' and returns the results in a form of an Iterator. The 'type' field tells the users the type of XML result returned. Possible values for 'type' are\: [ELEMENT, ATTRIBUTE, TEXT, OTHER]. This powerful operation can be used to retrieve XML Elements, Attributes, Text or filter based on element names, paths, attributes etc. The World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) organization provides the XPath specification (http\://www.w3.org). 

NOTE\: XML using default namespace is not supported by this operation.

Inputs\:
xml - The XML (in the form of a String).
xpathExpression - The XPath expression to evaluate.

Responses\:
has more - Another result was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - Something went wrong.
no more - No more results. This will only be returned once, then iteration restarts.

Returns\:
returnResult - Result evaluated from the XPath expression provided.
type - The type of result.
attributeName - If an attribute is returned, the name of the attribute.

91a85c12-884e-40d4-9f86-3a2a2ec1a44c.8e089f34-a42e-4326-8591-eaa1c3294afc.prompt=Enter a value for sublist 91a85c12-884e-40d4-9f86-3a2a2ec1a44c.9f81d25d-ab50-480a-821f-15607ba7ab55.prompt=Enter a value for value1 91a85c12-884e-40d4-9f86-3a2a2ec1a44c.a168ba89-af02-4daa-bb00-65bd2ada325b.description=
Service to perform an HTTP GET via the Java HTTP Client

Inputs\:
url - the url to attempt to retrieve.
username - the username to authenticate to url with.
password - the password for username.
timeout - a timeout after which the connection should be terminated, or 0 for no timeout.
useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. valid options are\: true/false
followRedirects - specifies whether or not the get command should automatically follow redirects.
trustAllRoots - enables weak security over SSL. A SSH certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it. valid options are\: true/false
proxy - a proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - a port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - a username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - a password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - perform URL encoding.
userAgent - if the HTTP header USER_AGENT needs to be overridden, pass in the value here
characterSet - the characterSet for HTTP Get request and response. Default is UTF-8.

Responses\:
success - URL retrieved successfully.
failure - The url could not be retrieved.
91a85c12-884e-40d4-9f86-3a2a2ec1a44c.a2b2c624-09f1-492a-9442-208ae6d954bc.description=Service to perform an HTTP PUT via the Java HTTP Client 
Inputs\:
url - the url to PUT from.
username - The username to use for basic authentication to the url
password - The password to use for basic authentication to the url
timeout - a timeout after which the connection should be terminated, or 0 for no timeout.
useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. Valid options are\: true/false
trustAllRoots - enables weak security over SSL. A SSH certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it. Valid options are\: true/false
proxy - a proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - a port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - a username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - a password to use when connecting to the proxy.
keystore - the path to the keystore to use for SSL Client Certificates
keystorePassword - the password for the keystore
encodeURL - perform URL encoding.
file - The file to put on the specified url.
userAgent - if the HTTP header USER_AGENT needs to be overridden, pass in the value here

Responses\:
success - The PUT command completed
failure - The PUT operation failed.

Result\:
The operation's return code.

ExtraResults\: 
resultText - the raw result of the operation
document - The Complete document returned by the PUT operation
pageLoadTimeInMS - The number of milliseconds it took the page to load.
responseTimeInMS - The number of milliseconds it took before the server responded.
URL - the url to PUT from
sessionId - the session ID of the connection to the host
exception - if an error occurred, the message of this error

91a85c12-884e-40d4-9f86-3a2a2ec1a44c.description=
This workflow updates a single resource utilization value for a resource modeled in a Resource Pool. Generally, this subflow would be called after querying the provider to determine the current utilization of a specific resource in CSA. The usedValue is passed into the subflow, along with the Resoure Pool identifier and the resource type.  The REST API call is made with the userIdentifier context.

Inputs-
resourcePoolId 	- Resource Pool ID. Resource pools may model multiple resources.
userIdentifier  	- User Identifier context used  to make the REST API call.  This is generally the OO Integration User
resourceType 	- Resource Type.  This value should match one of the enumerated resource types, e.g. CPU,MEMORY, STORAGE, VLAN etc
usedValue 		- Total resource consumed or released to CSA. This value will be positive number if resource is consumed by CSA and negative number if resource is release
		 from CSA. CSA utlization will be debited/credited from total utilization based on positive or negative values.
authType 		- The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
		valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
		Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
kerberosConfFile 	- The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
timeout 		- The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite 	timeout.Default value\: 0.
useCookies 		- If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true.
proxy 		- A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort 		- The port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername	 - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword	 - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL		 - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
userAgent		 - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
trustAllRoots		 - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: true
keystore		 - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client authentication is not to be used.
keystorePassword 	- Password to unlock the keystore.
trustKeystore	 - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
trustPassword	 - Password to unlock the truststore.

Outputs-
document  		– returned XML document from API
91a85c12-884e-40d4-9f86-3a2a2ec1a44c.e3f4e87e-97f9-4bb1-9c07-e5ec88e3f69d.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults". As a result, the context key whose name is in the keyName input will be appended with the string from the input resultText.

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Returns\:
The the value of the context variable it appended to.

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
